                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1301-1">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1301-1">AMS, IV, 137- 41 ; BHO, 423.
Suhadii ', I, 355- 56.
Peeters, "Passionnaire", 284-89.
BS, VI, 428- 29 (J.-M. Sauget).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Jacob was a Priest of Beth Naggare near Adiabene who was martyred with the deacon <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1620">Azad</persName>  during the persecution of Shapur II. The executioner washed his bloody sword in a pool, and the blood desiccated the pool.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1301-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on Apr. 14..</desc>
                    </event>
                    <note type="disambiguation">the priest, with Azad the deacon</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1301-1" source="#bib1301-1">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Yaʿqōb is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/327">Jacob and Azad (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
